I believe God did, in fact, put the universe in motion. I believe God created the first human and loves his people with all that is within him.<br>
<br>
I believe that the more we attempt to cut God out of our individual and societal lives the more he grants us that wish.<br>
<br>
I believe that God has watched man take his gifts and twist them to his own ends or tried to come up with a more forgiving lord, overseer or greater power that is congruent with their own beliefs. Some people see fit to fashion a god in their own image. <br>
<br>
Before the birth of Christ, many people asked the same questions they are asking today. Where is God? Why does he not help us? We need proof dont we?<br>
<br>
To prove to us that he loves us he led his people out of Egypt. He provided prophets to give us hope. He sent his only son to die in our place. As for proof, every man must decide what he wants to be and, more importantly, what realities he wants and does not want to see.<br>
<br>
I've heard some believe that in a universe disposed to entrophy and chaos that mankind is a backwater eddy in the laws of thermodynamics and physics. We're an accident and our ancestors just happened to get cosmically lucky and come into being.<br>
<br>
I cannot force myself into that belief. I have to believe there is a clockmaker that wound up the universe and is still in the shop. I often ponder, in the nature of chaos, just how many times I would have to throw a dissembled watch into the air before it would land on the table in front of me assembled and ticking. How much more complicated is a woman than a watch?<br>
<br>
So every member of the family of mankind must ask himself, what are you? Are you an beneficial accident and a creation of simply your mother and father and when you are no more that is the end?<br>
<br>
Or, was there a guiding hand that made us and created what we are today?<br>
<br>
I cannot bear to believe that we are an accident. What a sad and lonely world this would be to know that as an accident there is no cosmic design for us, no goals and no future?<br>
<br>
I appreciate that not everyone will think that way. I can see clear arguments that point to evolution of man, worship of other gods and differing religious beliefs as an open and shut case.<br>
<br>
But to see medical professionals post here who have been so blessed with surgeon's hands, people who play EQ with beautiful, healthy infants sleeping in the next room and husbands and wives who are perfect for one another who could not imagine being married to anyone else...I dont see how people cannot see some powerful being moving in their lives.<br>
<br>
Of course evolution should be taught in schools. But just like the religion of science, one cannot demand that God be pushed into a corner. Those who truly wish to debate would consider Creationism and Evolution of man as two theories for which there is both proof and lack of proof.<br>
<br>
The Christians who post here are doing as their God has commanded them, they are asking that you listen to their side of the issue. If you dont care to hear that theory, that is your right.<br>
<br>
But nobody is cramming religion down your throat or trying to indoctrinate your children into fairy tales. Christians have staked their eternal souls on trying to reach people like you.<br>
<br>
Why? So you can ridicule them and make them feel bad? So you can use every opportunity to make them feel stupid and worthless? So you can promote a do-what-you-like ethos?<br>
<br>
When questions like this arise, Christians are compelled to present the version of ancestry that God has revealed to them. Such is the way it is, and will be forever.<br>
<br>
One day every man will be asked to give an accounting of his life and beliefs. I hope to be able to say that I lived according to his will, not my own, no matter how much I wanted to do and believe things my way.<br>
<br>
Hess <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usijandistraightarrow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sijandistraightarrow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/31/02 12:16:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1576.topic&index=323>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Banning evolution: It's the Law....</span><hr size=1> Bravo, Hess. Another insightful post contributing to the discussion. I wish I were so articulate.<br>
