<br>
&quot;My feeling as a Christian points me to my Lord and Savior as a fighter,&quot; said Hitler, in one 1922 speech. &quot;It points me to the man who once in loneliness, surrounded by only a few followers, recognized these Jews for what they were and summoned me to fight against them. In boundless love, as a Christian and as a man, I read through the passage which tells us how the Lord rose at last in His might and seized the scourge to drive out of the Temple the brood of vipers and adders.&quot; <br>
<br>
In &quot;Mein Kampf,&quot; Hitler went one terrifying step further as he attacked the &quot;Jewish doctrine of Marxism.&quot; He wrote: &quot;Eternal Nature inexorably revenges the transgressions against her laws. Therefore, I believe today that I am acting in the sense of the Almighty Creator: By warding off the Jews, I am fighting for the Lord's work.&quot; <br>
<br>
<br>
The above paragraphs were the most interesting to me.<br>
<br>
I admire anyone who studies their religion and can discuss it intelligently. I've know many wonderful people who lived their lives as Christ taught, some called themselves Christian, some didn't. <br>
<br>
Faith in your beliefs is fine with me, but the formal, organized religion calling itself Christianity in all it's forms is a perversion the world would be better off without, in my opinion.<br>
<br>
To answer the question, I have yet to find an organized group identifying itself as Christian mirroring the first century church as described by the disciples, converts and other individuals in  available writings, not just the scriptures.<br>
<br>
The belief systems I've studied about, which in my opinion adhere most closely to the original church would have to include the Quaker and Amish groups. That's not to say I think they exactly mirror the first century church, just that they tend to be closest in my opinion. Man changes everything he comes in contact with, so it is with religion also. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usijandistraightarrow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sijandistraightarrow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/31/02 12:25:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1576.topic&index=324>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Banning evolution: It's the Law....</span><hr size=1> I found this very interesting site. Only read this page itself, but it looks interesting. Lots of spelling errors tho'.<br>
